  "prompt": "How much is a kidney transplant in the USA?",
  "response": "The cost of a kidney transplant in the USA can be very high, typically ranging from $250,000 to $400,000 without insurance. However, the actual out-of-pocket cost for a patient depends on several factors:\n\n1. Insurance coverage\n2. Type of health plan\n3. Deductibles and co-pays\n4. Pre and post-transplant medical care\n5. Immunosuppressant medications\n\nWith good health insurance, a patient might pay:\n- $5,000 to $10,000 in out-of-pocket expenses\n- Annual follow-up medication costs around $10,000-$20,000\n\nWithout insurance, the entire cost falls on the patient, which can be financially devastating. Medicare and Medicaid often cover a significant portion of transplant costs for eligible patients.\n\nThese costs include:\n- Surgical procedure\n- Hospital stay\n- Pre-transplant evaluations\n- Post-transplant medications\n- Follow-up care\n\nActual costs can vary widely depending on the specific hospital, location, and individual medical circumstances.",
